 sights of emerald rivers that have carved out some impressively magnificent rock formations. Zion actually boasts a great deal of environmental diversity. Aside from the desert expanses and red rock caves that the park has become known for, the park also contains large sections of woodland and forested areas. It’s variety in the ecosystems it offers is yet another reason to add Zion to your National Park bucket list.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/Live-Out_The-Outdoor-Social-Network-_Bucket-List-Ideas_Acadia-National-Park_Maine.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-98\" src=\"http://localhost/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/Live-Out_The-Outdoor-Social-Network-_Bucket-List-Ideas_Acadia-National-Park_Maine.jpg\" alt=\"Picturesque Acadia National Park Shoreline\" width=\"400\" height=\"256\" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Acadia National Park, Maine</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nArguably the natural gem of the East Coast, Acadia National Park is comprised of a series of heavily wooded islands off the coast of Maine. It’s considerably smaller than the other parks on the list, but it still offers great opportunities for camping nonetheless. Though it is small, the miles of coastline and the fact that it is located in one of the most beautiful areas of the East Coast have given Acadia a reputation for providing some of the most memorable views imaginable.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/Live-Out_The-Outdoor-Social-Network-_Bucket-List-Ideas_Denali-National-Park_Alaska.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-99\" src=\"http://localhost/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/Live-Out_The-Outdoor-Social-Network-_Bucket-List-Ideas_Denali-National-Park_Alaska.jpg\" alt=\"Lake on Alaska\" width=\"400\" height=\"266\" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Denali National Park, Alaska</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAlaska just very well may be the most naturally beautifu