en','open','','live-out_the-outdoor-social-network_deal_ski-and-snowboarding-gear_cole-sport','','','2015-02-25 19:32:43','2015-02-25 19:32:43','',109,'http://localhost/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/Live-Out_The-Outdoor-Social-Network_Deal_Ski-and-Snowboarding-Gear_Cole-Sport.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(242,1,'2015-02-25 19:32:52','2015-02-25 19:32:52','&nbsp;\r\n\r\nRECON Instruments has recently developed the world’s first Micro Optics Displays for ski goggles. The device uses built-in GPS &amp; sensors to display stats like speed, vertical descent, air time, altitude, navigation and distance, providing you with real-time stats as you blast down the mountain - and it fits conveniently into goggles made by just about every leading brand including Burton, K2 and Ride.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nRecon’s sensors can be embedded in the sides of your goggles out of your line of vision so as not to be distracting or dangerous. It allows you to retain visibility while the information is displayed in your peripheral area, like having a mini LCD screen in the side of your mask that’s there when you need it and out of sight when you don’t.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nUsing inbuilt GPS, the MOD Live can determine your location to within a meter. The on-board altimeter tracks your elevation while the gyroscope and accelerometer track your orientation and speed allowing you to trace your every shred on the slopes.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAlthough initially created for alpine skiers, the many advantages of this type of technology are quickly being recognized in other extreme sports – like sky sports. In the past, professional hang gliding and paragliding pilots use flight computers to provide them with detailed, real-time information about the skies they’re flying and have yet to utilize this new technology until recently. Considering the many preparations, safety measures, and calculations to consider when planning a jump, The MOD Live heads-up display provides an additional level of calculation and safety to the equation for wingsuit pilots as it delivers important flight information like speed, glide rate, and altitude in real time at a simple glance.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nRecon Live can also be linked to a wireless video camera through Bluetooth, allowing you to film your experiences while simultaneously tracking your analytic data. The Micro Optic Display will even connect to your smartphone so you cou can access your music playlist without removing your phone from your pocket - super gnarly.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThe MOD Live runs off of Android OS so you can upload your apps to it and it even comes with several relevant ones – like navigation and buddy tracking. A wireless remote control allows you to navigate between apps and interact with the Micro Optics Display and when the day is done you can upload all your stats online to sites like Live Out: The Outdoor Social Network.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAlrighty then, the RECON MOD Live Display - add it to your snowboarding gear wishlist. Cole Sports is your go-to for ski &amp; snowboarding deals if you need some fresh gear: <a href=\"http://goo.gl/Ab1A9E\">http://goo.gl/Ab1A9E</a>. Now get off your butt, throw on your Burton goggles, and get out there and get shredding!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nArticle by Charlie West\r\nContributor, Live Out: The Outdoor Social Network\r\n<a href=\"http://www.liveout.org\">http://www.liveout.org</a>','Ski & Snowboarding Gear Review: MOD Live Micro Optic Display by RECON','','inherit','open','open','','109-revision-v1','','','2015-02-25 19:32:52','2015-02-25 19:32:52','',109,'http://localhost/blog/109-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(243,1,'2015-02-26 14:33:01','2015-02-26 14:33:01','&nbsp;\r\n\r\nRECON Instruments has recently developed the world’s first Micro Optics Displays for ski goggles. The device uses built-in GPS &amp; sensors to display stats like speed, vertical descent, air time, altitude, navigation and distance, providing you with real-time stats as 