n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=x76VEPXYaI0\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSo we sat down Kelly to hear about his plans, goals, and passion for mountain biking...\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>What motivates you to ride &amp; what do you enjoy most about it?</strong>\r\n\r\nI guess one of the main things I enjoy about riding is sessioning with my mates, its always fun and motivates me to get my bike out and go shred.. We have plenty of laughs when we are riding and that\'s what its all about!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>How do you normally find new places to ride?</strong>\r\n\r\nI normally find new places to ride by talking to friends who tell me about new areas they have ridden recently, but if I\'m scoping out new free ride zones I check out Google maps and satellite photos to search for awesome terrain and scree slopes etc.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>What\'s your all-time favorite trail &amp; why?</strong>\r\n\r\nMy fav trail is called \"Rude Rock\" its here in Queenstown its flowwy and has great views!\r\n\r\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>What\'s your favorite trick &amp; the trick you find most challenging?</strong>\r\n\r\nMy fav trick is probably a big ol floaty Back flip on a BIG jump! and the trick I find the most challenging is Tailwhips, they annoy me a lot!\r\n\r\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>How has the sport evolved since you started riding? Do you hope it will continue to evolve &amp; if so, in what new directions can you see it going?</strong>\r\n\r\nYeah our sport is so young really, equipment, riding style, riding amplitude and tricks have progressed hugely over the last few years. As the sport evolves more we are only going to see things getting wilder!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>What career achievement you are most proud of?</strong>\r\n\r\nI am pretty stoked on my 2nd place at Red Bull Rampage last year, it the gnarliest comp of the year and it was a pretty big honor to stand on the podium!\r\n\r\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>What is your ultimate goal as a rider?</strong>\r\n\r\nI think my ultimate goal is to have fun!, if its not fun there is no point in doing it if you are not stoked. I also love to ride my bike on terrain that has never been ridden before.\r\n\r\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>What\'s the #1 thing to do / place to visit on your Bucket List?</strong>\r\n\r\nI want to travel to Africa at some point, I would love to check out the culture, go for a surf ( hopefully avoiding donating my leg to a shark!) ride my bike and most of all check out the wildlife.\r\n\r\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>What are some of your other outdoor hobbies besides riding?</strong>\r\n\r\nI like to surf, we live 2 hours away from the waves but when the forecast is good we head out there. I love being on the coast and its good to have a chill off the bike every now and then.\r\n\r\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Gotta ask, What was going through your head just before you did the back flip over the canyon at the 2013 Red Bull Rampage? Did you plan it, or did it it just sort of happen in the moment?</strong>\r\n\r\nHahah I have had that question a few times... Yeah I did plan it, I thought about it for a while... I was mostly reminding myself to \"spin slow,spin slow\" it was such a big jump I knew I didn\'t need to pull back much at all, it was awesome feeling I want to do it again!\r\n\r\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>What does the expression Live Out mean to you?</strong>\r\n\r\nGet outside and live your dream!\r\n\r\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Would you consider using Live Out to find new trails when you come to the U.S.?</strong>\r\n\r\nYeah for sure, it\'s sometimes hard when you are traveling to find places to shred and people to shred them with, Live Out is a good way to get in touch with people that want to do the same stuff as you do.\r\n\r\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\r\n\r\nConnect with Kelly!\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/kellymcgarrymtb?fref=nf\">https://www.facebook.com/kellymcgarrymtb?fref=nf</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://twitter.com/kellymcgazza\">https://twitter.com/kellymcgazza</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://instagram.com/kellymcgazza/\">https://instagram.com/kellymcgazza/</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nInterview by Scott McGuire\r\n\r\nWriter, Live Out: The Outdoor Social Network\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.liveout.org\">http://www.liveout.org</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>About Live Out</strong>\r\n\r\nLive Out is a new web-app &amp; social network where you can find people with outdoor interests, discover the best places to go &amp; find fun things to do outdoors near you.','Catching Up With Pro Mountain Biker Kelly McGarry','','inherit','open','open','','30-revision-v1','','','2015-02-25 21:32:23','2015-02-25 21:32:23','',30,'http://localhost/blog/30-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(282,1,'2015-02-25 21:33:25','2015-02-25 21:33:25','&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWe recently had the chance to catch up with professional mountain biker &amp; GoPro athlete Kelly McGarry. You may remember Kelly from last year\'s Red Bull Rampage as the guy who busted out a back-flip over the 72-ft canyon during the middle of his silver medal run. In case you missed it, check out this rad video:\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=x76VEPXYaI0\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSo we sat down Kelly to hear about his plans, goals, and passion for mountain biking...\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>What motivates you to ride &amp; what do you enjoy most about it?</strong>\r\n\r\nI guess one of the main things I enjoy about riding is sessioning with my mates, its always fun and motivates me to get my bike out and go shred.. We have plenty of laughs when we are riding and that\'s what its all about!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>How do you normally find new places to ride?</strong>\r\n\r\nI normally find new places to ride by talking to friends who tell me about new areas they have ridden recently, but if I\'m scoping out new free ride zones I check out Google maps and satellite photos to search for awesome terrain and scree slopes etc.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>What\'s your all-time favorite trail &amp; why?</strong>\r\n\r\nMy fav trail is called \"Rude Rock\" its here in Queenstown its flowwy and has great views!\r\n\r\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>What\'s your favorite trick &amp; the trick you find most challenging?</strong>\r\n\r\nMy fav trick is probably a big ol floaty Back flip on a BIG jump! and the trick I find the most challenging is Tailwhips, they annoy me a lot!\r\n\r\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>How has the sport evolved since you started riding? Do you hope it will continue to evolve &amp; if so, in what new directions can you see it going?</strong>\r\n\r\nYeah our sport is so young really, equipment, riding style, riding amplitude and tricks have progressed hugely over the last few years. As the sport evolves more we are only going to see things getting wilder!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>What career achievement you are most proud of?</strong>\r\n\r\nI am pretty stoked on my 2nd place at Red Bull Rampage last year, it the gnarliest comp of the year and it was a pretty big honor to stand on the podium!\r\n\r\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>What is your ultimate goal as a rider?</strong>\r\n\r\nI think my ultimate goal is to have fun!, if its not fun there is no point in doing it if you are not stoked. I also love to ride my bike on terrain that has never been ridden before.\r\n\r\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>What\'s the #1 thing to do / place to visit on your Bucket List?</strong>\r\n\r\nI want to travel to Africa at some point, I would love to check out the culture, go for a surf ( hopefully avoiding donating my leg to a shark!) ride my bike and most of all check out the wildlife.\r\n\r\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>What are some of your other outdoor hobbies besides riding?</strong>\r\n\r\nI like to surf, we live 2 hours away from the waves but when the forecast is good we head out there. I love being on the coast and its good to have a chill off the bike every now and then.\r\n\r\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Gotta ask, What was going through your head just before you did the back flip over the canyon at the 2013 Red Bull Rampage? Did you plan it, or did it it just sort of happen in the moment?</strong>\r\n\r\nHahah I have had that question a few times... Yeah I did plan it, I thought about it for a while... I was mostly reminding myself to \"spin slow,spin slow\" it was such a big jump I knew I didn\'t need to pull back much at all, it was awesome feeling I want to do it again!\r\n\r\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>What does the expression Live Out mean to you?</strong>\r\n\r\nGet outside and live your dream!\r\n\r\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Would you consider using Live Out to find new trails when you come to the U.S.?</strong>\r\n\r\nYeah for sure, it\'s sometimes hard when you are traveling to find places to shred and people to shred them with, Live Out is a good way to get in touch with people that want to do the same stuff as you do.\r\n\r\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\r\n\r\nConnect with Kelly!\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/kellymcgarrymtb?fref=nf\">https://www.facebook.com/kellymcgarrymtb?fref=nf</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://twitter.com/kellymcgazza\">https://twitter.com/kellymcgazza</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://instagram.com/kellymcgazza/\">https://instagram.com/kellymcgazza/</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nInterview by Scott McGuire\r\n\r\nWriter, Live Out: The Outdoor Social Network\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.liveout.org\">http://www.liveout.org</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>About Live Out</strong>\r\n\