re adamant about not having music for sing-a-long purposes, you can invest in an armband music holder for a device that plays out loud from Target or Bestbuy, or you can make one yourself like <a href=\"http://www.cnet.com/how-to/diy-a-dead-simple-workout-armband/\">this</a>.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>#4 Buddy System</strong>\r\n\r\nPeople are less likely to be attacked if they are not alone. I occasionally bring a buddy along, one that can keep up anyways. While I do prefer to go it alone, I understand that being 5’3’’ and 115 lbs. makes me an easy target. These next tips are precautions to take if heading out solo.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>#5 Keep your ID on hand</strong>\r\n\r\nIf an incident does occur when you’re out, it is best to have an ID on you. In a matter involving the police or an ambulance they need to identify you to call your emergency contacts. Very intense, I know.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>#6 Carry a cellphone</strong>\r\n\r\nMake sure your I.C.E. or “in case of emergency” numbers are easily accessed for you or a helpful stranger. Also, if you have a less than perfect sense of direction, your phone’s GPS may come in handy. Program the route you’re taking before you head out and you’re set.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nNow I know this may seem like a lot to think about, but trust me taking the proper safety precautions can help free your worries and allow you to get more enjoyment out of your run.\r\n\r\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Angela-Bell_Live-Out_The-Outdoor-Social-Network.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-522\" src=\"http://localhost/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Angela-Bell_Live-Out_The-Outdoor-Social-Network.png\" alt=\"Angela Bell\" width=\"180\" height=\"180\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Author: Angela Bell</strong>\r\n\r\nContributor, Live Out: The Outdoor Social Network\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>About</strong>\r\n\r\nAngela is graduating senior majoring in Mass Communications and minoring in Creative Writing. In the future, she plans to get her MA in Publishing and Writing and travel overseas for volunteer work. Her hobbies include running, filming, and writing.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','6 Safety Tips for Night Running','','inherit','open','open','','521-revision-v1','','','2015-03-21 16:48:21','2015-03-21 16:48:21','',521,'http://localhost/blog/521-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(531,1,'2015-03-22 18:48:43','2015-03-22 18:48:43','<div class=\"banner\"><a href=\"http://localhost:8080/liveout/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Live-Out_The-Outdoor-Social-Network_Spring-Giveaway.png\"><img class=\"banner-image\" src=\"http://localhost:8080/liveout/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Live-Out_The-Outdoor-Social-Network_Spring-Giveaway.png\" alt=\"Live Out 2.0 Giveaway\"/></a></div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"w-clearfix contest-burner\">\r\n      <div class=\"form-header\">How did you hear about us?</div>\r\n      <div class=\"form-text\">Your friend earns 50 points when you type their name in the box.</div>\r\n      <div class=\"w-form\">\r\n        <form class=\"w-clearfix\" id=\"email-form\" name=\"email-form\" data-name=\"Email Form\">\r\n          <input class=\"w-input input-field\" id=\"name\" type=\"text\" placeholder=\"Enter your friends name\" name=\"name\" data-name=\"Name\"><a class=\"buttons wp-form-buttons\" href=\"#\" data-ix=\"show-temporarily-offline-message\">SUBMIT</a>\r\n        </form>\r\n        <div class=\"w-form-done\">\r\n          <p>Thank you! Your submission has been received!</p>\r\n        </div>\r\n        <div class=\"w-form-fail\">\r\n          <p>Oops! Something went wrong while submitting the form :(</p>\r\n        </div>\r\n      </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"page-title\">Enter here!</div>\r\n<div class=\"h3\">Win FREE GEAR for telling people about Live Out!</div>\r\n<div class=\"normal-text\">Click <a class=\"links points\" href=\"http://liveout.org/blog/contest-points\">HERE</a> to learn h