door-Social-Network.jpg\" alt=\"Kendall Eisenberg\" width=\"180\" height=\"180\" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Kendall Eisenberg</strong>\r\n\r\nContributor, Live Out: The Outdoor Social Network\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>About</strong>\r\n\r\nKendall is a freshman at the University of Miami studying entrepreneurship. With a motto of “try everything at least once,” she’s participated in soccer, basketball, rock climbing, rowing, and much more. Her hobbies include traveling, writing, reading, and sports.','Fitness Trackers: Are They Worth it?','','inherit','open','open','','545-revision-v1','','','2015-03-23 19:57:01','2015-03-23 19:57:01','',545,'http://localhost/blog/545-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(552,1,'2015-03-23 20:01:42','2015-03-23 20:01:42','Tracks your steps, calories burned, distance traveled, active minutes and sleep. ','Fitness Tracker_Review_Live Out_The Outdoor Social Network_Blog','','inherit','open','open','','fitness-tracker_review_live-out_the-outdoor-social-network_blog','','','2015-03-23 20:02:12','2015-03-23 20:02:12','',545,'http://localhost/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/Fitness-Tracker_Review_Live-Out_The-Outdoor-Social-Network_Blog.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(553,1,'2015-03-23 20:13:46','2015-03-23 20:13:46','Fitness trackers sometimes have a little bit of controversy surrounding them. Their accuracy and efficiency have been debated since they first came to market. Even after deciding to get one, there are many trackers to choose from and most of them aren’t cheap.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAt first I was like everyone else. I couldn’t decide if I really wanted to pay a hundred dollars for something that was a glorified pedometer and an ugly accessory. I decided to let other people be the guinea pigs and wait for new bands with better technology.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nA year or so into the fitness tracker fad, I began to ask people what they thought of their trackers. Of all the people I asked, not one of them regretted get