tteries as the old ones. Headlamps are even better because then you can look directly at the driver.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\r\n<ol start=\"2\">\r\n <li>Wave &amp; yell.  If you can\'t make eye contact with the driver, wave &amp; yell at them. You might feel embarrassed, but it’s better than getting hit!</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\r\n<ol start=\"3\">\r\n <li>Slow down. If you can\'t get the driver’s attention, slow down - even stop if you have to.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\r\n<ol start=\"4\">\r\n <li>Ride further left. Yup, left. Especially on slow roads with many cross streets, you\'ll want to ride farther left. The further left you are the more likely the driver will see you. You might be worried this will make you more vulnerable to cars coming from behind, but you\'re far more likely to get hit by a car at an intersection ahead of you that can\'t see you, than from a car behind you which can see you clearly. On fast roadways with few intersections, you\'ll want to stay further right.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\r\n\r\nAlrighteythen, hope you got something out of this.. Now get out there and ride!\r\n\r\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<b>Author: Charlie West</b>\r\n\r\nWriter, Live Out: The Outdoor Social Network\r\n\r\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<b>About</b>\r\n\r\nCharlie is an outdoor enthusiast and blogger. He enjoys “doing epic sh*t.”\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Glow-in-the-Dark Spray for Cycling at Night','','publish','open','open','','glow-in-the-dark-spray-for-cycling-at-night','','','2015-04-07 22:16:50','2015-04-07 22:16:50','',0,'http://localhost/blog/?p=606',0,'post','',0),(607,1,'2015-04-07 21:56:38','2015-04-07 21:56:38','Reflective spray for cycling at night','Volvo-lifepaint-reflective spray for cycling at night','','inherit','open','open','','volvo-lifepaint-reflective-spray-for-cycling-at-night','','','2015-04-07 21:56:56','