that produces results. This is true, but it is also an excellent way to keep your workout exciting. Many people think this saying refers to weight training only. But if you have been weight training for a month straight with no other activity, maybe it is time to confuse your muscles in a new way. If you have a gym membership that offers a variety of fitness classes, go to some! Put your money to good use by taking a yoga class Monday, a cycling class Tuesday, and a boxing class Wednesday! If you don’t have a membership, many local organizations provide fun fitness classes. Check out your local martial arts center and pay a one time fee for a workout that you will learn something during. Do Zumba at your local dance studio. Or even visit a Curves gym nearby. Yes, none of these are related. And yes, you will probably be working out with people you have never met before. But finding some random classes near you can be a great way to take a break from your everyday Insanity DVDs or your normal weightlifting regimen. It is also fun to learn new things with people you normally wouldn’t surround yourself with. Plus, you will probably end up working out body parts you forgot you had.\r\n\r\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<b>Change your workout schedule.</b>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThis may be an obvious option, but if you normally have a legs day, then an arms day, take a day to combine both, and do it in a location your normally wouldn’t. It will add an extra edge to your workout and the different level of intensity will be a nice change. If you have been repeating the same daily routine for a few months, change up the schedule or add on extra days or longer hours. Schedule your workout with a friend. Or workout in the morning instead of at night. Simple changes can lead to a big difference in the way you mentally prepare for a workout.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Get outside.</b>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nCuring workout boredom could be as simple as taking a hike when you would normally take a yoga class. Or throw in a long trail run when would normally be in the gym. Climb that mountain you have been thinking about for a year. Adding some fresh air and new views really invigorates your body and mind in a way you may have forgotten about during your winter workout videos.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Add a new challenge. </b>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAnother simple way to add a tougher element could even just be to add a balance challenge to your normal weights workout. Try performing your moves slowly and accurately on a Bosu ball or a stability ball. Keep your good form at all costs, so transition slowly. Adding balance to the mix can work your muscles in new, refreshing ways and make things more fun.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Get a new playlist.       </b>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nMusic can really help you push through when you are worn out. Listening to your favorite jams helps you tune out the voices in your head telling you it is not possible to complete another rep. But sometimes your favorite songs start all sounding the same. Have a friend with different music tastes than you make you a new workout playlist. The choices will surprise you and keep you listening when you would otherwise be focusing on how impossible your workout feels. If you end up hating their song choices, that is okay too. The anger will fuel your workout until you can get back to the music you like next time.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nHopefully these tips will give you some easy fixes to boring workout days. For more great ideas, check out this article on <a href=\"http://thoughtcatalog.com/tina-alexander/2014/03/15-ways-to-make-working-out-fun-really/\">15 Ways To Make Working Out Fun</a>.\r\n\r\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://localhost/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/syd-kingrea-writer-live-out-the-outdoor-social-network.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-641\" src=\"http://localhost/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/syd-kingrea-writer-live-out-the-outdoor-social-network.jpg\" alt=\"syd kingrea\" width=\"180\" height=\"168\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Author: Syd Kingrea</strong>\r\n\r\nContributor, Live Out: The Outdoor Social Network\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>About</strong>\r\n\r\nSydnah is a freelance writer, videographer, and photographer. As a fitness and nutrition enthusiast, she practices daily exercise and follows a whole food diet. She encourages spending as much time as possible outdoors, while also preserving and respecting nature. Her philosophy is to always keep your workout routine, and your life, new and exciting.','Ways to Spice Up Your Workout Routine','','publish','open','open','','ways-to-spice-up-your-workout-routine','','\nhttp://thoughtcatalog.com/tina-alexander/2014/03/15-ways-to-make-working-out-fun-really/','2015-04-10 00:16:04','2015-04-10 00:16:04','',0,'http://localhost/blog/?p=615',0,'post','',0),(616,1,'2015-04-09 18:08:28','2015-04-09 18:08:28','','Tup2ixKn5KocPpoNM1pJ_685lquH-myGfxNwcLl4z7k','','inherit','open','open','','tup2ixkn5kocpponm1pj_685lquh-mygfxnwcll4z7k','','','2015-04-09 18:08:28','2015-04-09 18:08:28','',615,'http://localhost/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Tup2ixKn5KocPpoNM1pJ_685lquH-myGfxNwcLl4z7k.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(617,1,'2015-04-09 18:08:43','2015-04-09 18:08:43','<a href=\"http://localhost/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Tup2ixKn5KocPpoNM1pJ_685lquH-myGfxNwcLl4z7k.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-616\" src=\"http://localhost/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Tup2ixKn5KocPpoNM1pJ_685lquH-myGfxNwcLl4z7k.jpg\" alt=\"Tup2ixKn5KocPpoNM1pJ_685lquH-myGfxNwcLl4z7k\" width=\"575\" height=\"348\" /></a>\r\n\r\nEveryone falls into slumps with their daily workouts. Whether it is just a drag to do the same old thing or you hit a plateau in your weight loss goals, don’t let boredom or disappointment mess up your game. Check out our tips for spicing things up.\r\n\r\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<b>Don’t be afraid