37:08','',644,'http://www.liveout.org/blog/644-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(658,1,'2015-04-12 18:39:06','2015-04-12 18:39:06','Jordan Spieth 2015 Masters','Jordan Spieth 2015 Masters','','inherit','open','open','','jordan-spieth-2015-masters-2','','','2015-04-12 18:39:17','2015-04-12 18:39:17','',644,'http://www.liveout.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Jordan-Spieth-2015-Masters1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(659,1,'2015-04-12 18:40:25','2015-04-12 18:40:25',' Round1 2015 Masters','Jordan Spieth Round 1 2015 Masters','','inherit','open','open','','jordan-spieth-round1-2015-masters','','','2015-04-12 18:40:34','2015-04-12 18:40:34','',644,'http://www.liveout.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Jordan-Spieth-Round1-2015-Masters.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(660,1,'2015-04-12 18:41:14','2015-04-12 18:41:14','&nbsp;\r\n\r\nJordan Spieth is 18 holes away from making Master history. Set to tee off at 2:50 pm, at 16 under par and a 4 shot lead he’ll try to hold off the likes of Phil Mickelson, Tiger Woods, and world #1 Rory McIlroy in pursuit of his first green jacket. Needless to say, it’s not over yet. As history has shown, anything can happen on Sunday at Augusta.\r\n\r\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\r\n\r\nThe 2015 Masters has already written some of the best storylines in recent Masters history.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.liveout.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Jordan-Spieth-2015-Masters.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-653\" src=\"http://www.liveout.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Jordan-Spieth-2015-Masters.jpg\" alt=\"Jordan Spieth\" width=\"534\" height=\"401\" /></a>\r\n\r\nPhoto: USA Today\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Spieth</b>\r\n\r\nSpieth, 21, has been locked in and on fire lately, coming in with two victories in his last 3 tournaments and taking 2nd in the other. After last years runner-up finish after holding a share of the lead on Sunday you better believe he’s learned and matured from the experi