 these great areas to explore, but you can also cool off on a hot day and enjoy the magnificent <b>waterfalls</b>. You must exercise proper caution around <b>waterfalls</b> however, since it’s easy to get hurt on them.\r\n\r\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<b>Wildlife Observation</b>\r\n\r\n<b>Western North Carolina</b> hosts a wide array of animal life, which can be seen out on nature trails and backroads. Small animals such as squirrels, chipmunks, and mice can be seen skittering across the forest floor. Larger animals can also be seen, such as deer, wild pigs, and even bears. If you don’t have the kind of patience that it takes to wait around for animals to show up, you can always visit the <b>WNC Nature Center</b> in <b>Asheville</b>. Here guests can find wolves, bears, otters, and even cougars.\r\n\r\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<b>Biking</b>\r\n\r\n<b>Asheville</b> also includes many good places to <b>bike</b>. Not only could you use your <b>bike</b> to explore urban and residential areas, but there are also <b>cycling</b> routes that take you through the forests. <b>Biking </b>in <b>Asheville</b> is a nice way to get your exercise in while exploring one of the most beautiful areas in the United States.\r\n\r\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<b>Stargazing</b>\r\n\r\nSince <b>Asheville</b> doesn’t produce much light pollution, it’s easy to find a place where you can turn your telescope to the sky to observe the glistening moon, stars, and planets. The surrounding <b>mountains </b>also provide high elevations and isolated areas for you to go and stare into the depths of the cosmos.\r\n\r\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\r\n\r\nAndrew McClure graduated from Western Carolina University with a B.A. in English, a concentration in professional writing, and a minor in biology. He is currently trying to enter the world of freelance writing. In his free time, he enjoys reading and studying alongside his dogs, Pepper and Little Ann.','Top Five Outdoor Activities in Asheville, North Carolina','','inherit','open','open','','729-revision-v1','','','2015-05-05 23:51:30','2015-05-05 23:51:30','',729,'http://www.liveout.org/blog/729-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(732,1,'2015-05-06 18:00:36','2015-05-06 18:00:36','&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAsheville, North Carolina is a lively city in the heart of Western North Carolina, where nature, culture, and urban life clash to form an eclectic atmosphere. Asheville has been touted as one of the best places to live in the United States, and tourists come from all over to experience Asheville. Here are top five activities that are available in the city of Asheville.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>Visit the Biltmore House</b>\r\n\r\nWhile in Asheville, you will definitely want to tour this sprawling estate. The enormous mansion was constructed by George Vanderbilt and is one of the many jewels in Asheville’s crown. Guests can go on extensive tours of the house to experience the amenities that Vanderbilt installed, which include a massive indoor pool, a bowling alley, an expansive library, and much more. A visit to Biltmore is an excellent way to explore the history of Asheville and to experience the ways that the super-rich lived in the early 20th century.\r\n\r\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<b>Go on a Tour</b>\r\n\r\nAsheville offers a wide range of tours. When my cousins and I were kids, we went on a ghost tour through the town, exploring some of the old buildings and locations that are said to have ghostly legends surrounding them. This was a fun way to learn about the history of the area and freak ourselves out at the same time. In addition, Asheville offers many other historical tours that you can find by looking through promotional materials on the area.\r\n\r\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<b>Peruse Local Businesses</b>\r\n\r\nThere are many small businesses to visit in Asheville. Not only do these stores and restaurants house unique businesses that embody the artistic atmosphere of Asheville, but it also helps the local economy when you shop at these places. Many of these businesses can be found in the downtown area, and they include clothing shops, toy stores, and arts and crafts stores.\r\n\r\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<b>Check Out the Art and Music Scene</b>\r\n\r\nAsheville also offers a lively art and music scene; there is an art museum that houses a wide array of artifacts. Viewing these items can be a relaxing and meditative experience, and doing so can help you become more attuned to the spirit of Asheville. In addition, it’s difficult to walk around town on a warm summer evening without hearing some independent musician playing their instrument on the sidewalk. Amazing concerts are often held as well. Be sure to check local listings to look these events up.\r\n\r\n<strong><strong> </strong></strong>\r\n\r\n<b>Explore Downtown</b>\r\n\r\nDowntown Asheville has an impressive architectural history, and you definitely won’t want to skip an exploration of the downtown area. The wide array of restaurants and shops provide hours of entertainment. When you go, make sure you are prepared to walk, since the area is a bit large.\r\n\r\nAndrew McClure graduated from Western Carolina University with a B.A. in English, a concentration in professional writing, and a minor in biology. He is currently trying to enter the world of freelance writing. In his free time, he enjoys reading and studying alongside his dogs, Pepper and Little Ann.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.liveout.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/andrew.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-734\" src=\"http://www.liveout.org/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/andrew.jpg\" alt=\"andrew\" width=\"180\" height=\"180\" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Author: Andrew McClure</strong>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>About</strong>\r\n\r\nAndrew McClure graduated from Western Carolina University with a B.A. in Englis